result.execSummary:
The defendant Teflon Z Bennett was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/Intent-Cocaine (>1-5g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(cm)1r.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Received and Filed. Notice of completion

CASE HEARD IN BRANCH 40 FOR BRANCH 16.
Defendant Teflon Z Bennett in court, in custody.  Attorney Sarah Zwach in court for Teflon Z Bennett.  Attorney Francesco Mineo in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for jury trial.  Parties have reached an agreement.  Plea negotiations set forth on the record and agreed upon by the parties.

AS TO COUNT 11:
Defendant changes plea to GUILTY. Defendant examined as to plea, advised of Constitutional Rights and the maximum penalties. Defendant further advised that if not a US citizen, deportation is possible. Court found that the defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived rights.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form, Addendum, and Elements/Jury Instructions received and filed. Parties stipulate to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant GUILTY and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Pursuant to plea negotiations and on the motion of the State, Court ordered COUNTS 10, 12, 13, AND 14 DISMISSED BUT READ IN for the purpose of sentencing.  

Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon, he may never own or possess a firearm.  Court advised defendant that he may not vote until his civil rights have been restored.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by the State, Defense Counsel, and Defendant.

AS TO COUNT 11:
The Court sentenced the defendant to 12 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 140 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges for work only.  The Court STAYED the sentence and placed the defendant on probation for 2 YEARS. 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION: 
- AODA assessment and follow through with any recommended treatment. 
- Provide DNA sample. 
- Full-time work/school (minimum of 30 hours of work per week if in school; must receive paychecks).
- Complete 60 hours of community service. 
- Complete a cognitive thinking program. 
- Obtain a valid driver's license. 

Court ordered the defendant to pay the DNA surcharge by the end of supervision.  Failure to pay shall result in a civil judgment.  Court waived all other court costs, fees, and surcharges due to a finding of indigency. 

20 day appeal rights given.
